John Njoroge , Bishop of Trans Nzoia diocese, has been elected the new archbishop of the African Independent Pentecostal Church of Kenya.He replaces John Baptista Mugecha who died of colon cancer in January, aged 72.The ceremony was conducted on Sunday at AIPCK Githunguri. Njoroge (pictured) defeated five other bishops who had applied for the position in an 11-day process under the church constitution.&ldquo;According to the church constitution, after the first archbishop died we mourned 30 days and spent 60 days praying for another archbishop,&rdquo; chairman George Njuruba said.&ldquo;Then 21 days for those interested to apply for the position, which we have fulfilled today as we have gotten a new archbishop.&rdquo;